"'''Crimson Bounty'''" is a short story that was co-written by [[Charlene Newcomb]] and [[Rich Handley]]. It was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 14|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 14]] by [[West End Games]] in [[August]] [[1997]].

==Plot summary==
The [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] duo of [[Celia Durasha]] and [[Kaj Nedmak]] is once again in trouble due to Kaj's wheeling and dealing and [[Gambling/Legends|gambling]]. Rather than smuggling illegal [[Weapon/Legends|weapons]] for [[Bwahl|Bwahl the Hutt]], Kaj delivers them to another [[Gangster/Legends|gangster]] to settle a debt. This sets [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] on his trail, including the deceptive and tenacious [[Thune (bounty hunter)|Thune]]. Thune captures Kaj and nearly apprehends Celia, but she is betrayed by [[U-THR|Uthre]], a [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] in Thune's employ. Free of Thune's pursuit, Kaj and Celia are reunited.

==Continuity==
''Crimson Bounty'' is a sequel to [[A Certain Point of View (short story)|''A Certain Point of View'']].

It was originally set [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]], however, in-text references to the story taking place 2 [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after the events on the [[Kuari Princess/Legends|''Kuari Princess'']] in ''A Certain Point of View'' mean this tale has to take place in [[2 ABY/Legends|2 ABY]].

